## Core Fishing Systems

### Water Body Simulation
The water system (`src/water/waterBodyTypes.js`) defines distinct water environments (Pond, River, Lake, Ocean) with unique characteristics affecting gameplay through flow dynamics, wave patterns, depth parameters and surface properties. Advanced rendering (`src/water/waterMaterial.js`) handles directional flow, depth-based transitions and environmental effects.

### Fishing Mechanics
Rod physics (`src/fishing/rod.js`, `src/fishing/aimRod.js`) implements spring-based tip animation responding to tension, natural micro-sway, and 45-degree forward aiming with environmental awareness. The camera system (`src/camera/cameraSpring.js`) provides fishing-specific positioning with water-aware constraints.

### Player Systems
The core progression mechanics include:
- 33 fish types across 5 rarity tiers
- Complex weight calculations based on player level/location
- Progressive difficulty scaling
- Dynamic experience rewards
- Multi-tiered achievement progression
- Category-specific completion tracking
- Location-based unlocking system
- Non-linear experience curves
- Multi-stat system affecting fishing success
- Dynamic fight duration based on fish properties

### Equipment 
Comprehensive tackle system organizing equipment into categories (rods, reels, lines, hooks, baits) with:
- Tier-based progression
- Level-gated unlocks
- Catch bonus calculations
- Custom timing windows
- Unique properties per category affecting gameplay mechanics

The business logic creates an integrated fishing simulation where water environments, equipment choices, player progression and fish behavior systems work together to create meaningful gameplay variation and progression.

